Difference between encryption and signing

Encryption protects the content of the file so that only the intended recipient can read it.
Signing proves who created the message and confirms that the content was not changed.

Role of public and private key

The public key is shared with others and is used to encrypt data or verify a signature. 
The private key is secret and is used to decrypt data and create a digital signature.

What happens when an encrypted file is modified

If an encrypted file is modified, decryption may fail or the output may be corrupted.
If the file was also signed, GPG will report that the signature is not valid, which shows that the file was changed.
